How to Connect to a Tinker Board from a Windows Computer Using VNC:

Install VNC Viewer on a Windows computer.
https://www.realvnc.com/en/connect/download/viewer/

Get TinkerBoard’s current IP address:
Desktop > Home Icon > System > LXTerminal

ip address

In Windows computer launch VNC Viewer:
  Go to: File > New Connection
  Enter the TinkerBoard’s current IP address.
  Followed by a colon and the default port number 5901
  Example: 192.168.1.1:5901
  Double click on the connection icon
  You should see a window open up with your TinkerBoard’s desktop visible.
